What's left to do is something about the tables, finally.

00:38:37.540 --> 00:38:40.699
So let's take a look at our goal.

00:38:40.699 --> 00:38:43.379
It looks like we want to find the top 30

00:38:43.379 --> 00:38:46.780
medals and bottom 30 medals.

00:38:46.780 --> 00:38:50.459
And then we're going to apply some formatting to that

00:38:50.459 --> 00:38:51.459
as well.

00:38:51.459 --> 00:38:55.500
So currently, our table over here

00:38:55.500 --> 00:39:00.060
gives us a single table of medals by country.

00:39:00.060 --> 00:39:03.260
So we're going to want to split this into two.

00:39:03.260 --> 00:39:07.060
And we are going to want the results of those

00:39:07.060 --> 00:39:09.100
across two tab sets.

00:39:09.100 --> 00:39:11.860
So how will we go about doing that?

00:39:11.860 --> 00:39:18.939
Let's, first of all, split the calculation into two.

00:39:18.939 --> 00:39:22.939
So instead of medals by country, we

00:39:22.939 --> 00:39:27.739
are going to update the label of this

00:39:27.739 --> 00:39:33.379
to say something like Summer Top 30 Total Medals.

00:39:36.500 --> 00:39:39.300
And it looks like we want to call it Top 30 Total

00:39:39.300 --> 00:39:40.379
Medals for the title.

00:39:44.300 --> 00:39:48.620
And then we're going to want to create something similar.

00:39:48.620 --> 00:39:50.659
And this is going to be Bottom 30.

00:39:53.379 --> 00:39:57.620
So let's go ahead and leave this for a second.

00:39:57.620 --> 00:40:00.939
And let's see, what would this look like with two code

00:40:00.939 --> 00:40:02.979
cells in this row?

00:40:02.979 --> 00:40:06.739
And we're going to then see, how do we put them across tab sets

00:40:06.739 --> 00:40:08.780
and then finally bring in the calculation?

00:40:08.780 --> 00:40:10.659
So we're in a row.

00:40:10.659 --> 00:40:13.500
And what it did is it sewed two code cells

00:40:13.500 --> 00:40:17.739
that both emit some output and hence put them across columns.

00:40:17.739 --> 00:40:20.580
But we want to say, do not put them across columns.

00:40:20.580 --> 00:40:23.580
Actually, put them across tab sets.

00:40:23.580 --> 00:40:26.659
So we're going to add the tab set class at the row level.

00:40:34.179 --> 00:40:38.780
And that basically gives me, if I pop this out

00:40:38.780 --> 00:40:41.179
to the browser, it's a little bit easier

00:40:41.179 --> 00:40:44.379
to see that we actually have the two tab sets now.

00:40:44.379 --> 00:40:48.139
It just so happens we have the same table in them for now.

00:40:48.139 --> 00:40:49.260
We'll fix that.

00:40:49.300 --> 00:40:52.379
But let's take a look at our inspiration.

00:40:52.379 --> 00:40:55.939
It also looks like we don't just want the table,

00:40:55.939 --> 00:40:58.860
but we also want some text in there as well.

00:40:58.860 --> 00:41:02.580
So team sorted in descending order of metals.

00:41:02.580 --> 00:41:07.300
And it's probably the ascending order on the other side.

00:41:07.300 --> 00:41:09.219
So let's go ahead and add that text.

00:41:09.659 --> 00:41:17.060
Sorted in descending order of metals for the top

00:41:17.060 --> 00:41:18.540
and for the bottom.

00:41:18.540 --> 00:41:22.459
That's going to say ascending order of metals.

00:41:22.459 --> 00:41:24.699
Now I have four pieces of content

00:41:24.699 --> 00:41:28.860
in this row that has a tab set class assigned to it.

00:41:28.860 --> 00:41:31.820
So what does that look when we render things?

00:41:31.820 --> 00:41:35.820
It actually places the text in its own tab

00:41:35.860 --> 00:41:38.179
as well, which is obviously not what we want.

00:41:38.179 --> 00:41:39.659
And because it doesn't have a table,

00:41:39.659 --> 00:41:43.060
it sort of gives it a placeholder table.

00:41:43.060 --> 00:41:47.780
But we know how to place some text and some R output

00:41:47.780 --> 00:41:49.100
into a single card.

00:41:49.100 --> 00:41:50.860
We've already done that here.

00:41:50.860 --> 00:41:55.060
So let's go ahead and use that same technique.

00:41:55.060 --> 00:41:56.860
Let's go back to where we had done that.

00:41:56.860 --> 00:42:00.820
So we did that by adding a card.

00:42:00.820 --> 00:42:03.820
So here I'm going to add a card.

00:42:04.260 --> 00:42:07.139
So here I'm going to add a card.

00:42:07.139 --> 00:42:13.020
And we can name this Top 30 Metals instead of naming

00:42:13.020 --> 00:42:14.899
our executable cell that.

00:42:19.459 --> 00:42:23.459
And similarly, add another card here

00:42:23.459 --> 00:42:28.100
that encapsulates that text that has the bottom 30

00:42:28.100 --> 00:42:31.739
metals as its title.

00:42:31.739 --> 00:42:35.219
And then we close the fences for that as well.

00:42:44.379 --> 00:42:45.300
All right.

00:42:45.300 --> 00:42:48.260
This is looking good, except that we now actually

00:42:48.260 --> 00:42:51.260
