00:42:51.260 --> 00:42:53.300
So let's go ahead and do that.

00:42:53.300 --> 00:43:00.739
We are going to say, before we actually turn it into a table,

00:43:00.739 --> 00:43:10.699
once we have arranged them, we want to take the top 30 rows.

00:43:10.699 --> 00:43:15.540
And then we can make a table out of those.

00:43:15.540 --> 00:43:18.020
And a few things that we might want to do

00:43:18.020 --> 00:43:21.620
is let's go ahead and align the columns.

00:43:21.620 --> 00:43:24.899
So we have two columns here.

00:43:24.899 --> 00:43:31.580
But we want the team name to be aligned on the left.

00:43:38.659 --> 00:43:43.580
So let's see what this would do if we

00:43:43.580 --> 00:43:48.459
were to do the same thing, except not in descending order

00:43:48.459 --> 00:43:53.659
for the second one, and do something similar in terms

00:43:53.699 --> 00:43:55.260
of the code cell content.

00:44:02.500 --> 00:44:03.540
And here we go.

00:44:03.540 --> 00:44:07.340
Now we actually have different content in here.

00:44:07.340 --> 00:44:11.179
And finally, one thing we did was

00:44:11.179 --> 00:44:14.580
